  overviewText="When a tooth is too damaged for a filling — due to extensive decay, a large crack, or previous root canal therapy — a crown provides full-coverage protection. It encases the entire visible portion of the tooth, restoring it to its original shape and function while shielding the weakened structure from further damage. Our all-porcelain, metal-free crowns are shade-matched using digital color analysis so they blend seamlessly with the surrounding teeth."
  overviewExtra="Patients throughout Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck choose Thrive Dental for dental crowns because of the precision we bring to every case. Rather than messy putty impressions, we use the iTero digital scanner to capture an exact 3D model of your bite — which is sent directly to our ceramist lab for fabrication. The result is a crown that fits accurately from the first seating, with minimal adjustment needed. If you have a cracked tooth, a failing old crown, or a tooth that recently had a root canal, don't wait — a crown placed promptly protects the tooth and typically prevents the need for extraction later."
